<h2>FAQs</h2>

<div class="faq">
    <h3>1. Can individuals with celiac disease consume Uncle Ben's Long Grain and Wild Rice?</h3>
    <p>While the ingredients in Uncle Ben's Long Grain and Wild Rice do not contain gluten, the product is not certified gluten-free and is processed in facilities that handle wheat. Therefore, individuals with celiac disease should exercise caution and consider certified gluten-free alternatives.</p>

    <h3>2. Are there any gluten-free alternatives to Uncle Ben's Long Grain and Wild Rice?</h3>
    <p>Yes, there are several gluten-free rice products available on the market. Look for brands that are certified gluten-free to ensure safety. Some options include Lundberg Family Farms and RiceSelect.</p>

    <h3>3. How can I verify if a product is gluten-free?</h3>
    <p>Check the product label for a gluten-free certification logo, such as the GFCO seal. Additionally, review the ingredient list and allergen statement for any mention of gluten-containing grains or cross-contamination risks.</p>
</div>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>

<p>In conclusion, Uncle Ben's Long Grain and Wild Rice does not contain gluten-containing ingredients, but it is not certified gluten-free and is processed in facilities that handle wheat. For individuals with celiac disease or severe gluten sensitivity, this presents a potential risk of cross-contamination. It is advisable to opt for certified gluten-free rice products to ensure safety. Always read labels carefully and consult with a healthcare professional if you have any doubts about a product's suitability for your dietary needs.</p>

